issue.title: Simple UI duckyscript does not work at all
issue.body:
<!-- READ THIS FIRST:
  Don't waste my time and yours. Please fill this in properly if you want help, otherwise your issue will be closed.

  - Make sure you are running the latest version of USB Army Knife before reporting an issue
  - Provide as many details as possible. Paste logs, configuration samples and code into the backticks.
  - We have a wiki and an FAQ, please read this first!
  DO NOT DELETE ANY TEXT from this template! Otherwise, your issue may be closed without comment.
-->
## Your problem
<!-- 
  Describe the issue you are experiencing here to communicate to the
  maintainers. Tell us what you were trying to do and what happened.
-->
The "Simple UI" duckyscript is not working whatsoever, seemingly hanging on "LOAD_DS_FILES_FROM_SD()"

## Your device
<!--
  Provide details about the device you are using such as as LilyGo T-Dongle S3
-->
```txt
Device: LilyGo T-Dongle S3
SD: 32GB Samsung EVO Select
```

# Language (HID attacks only)
<!--
  What language is your device configured to use?
  What keyboard layout is your victim machine using?
-->
N/A


## Your DuckyScript
<!--
Please provide any DuckyScript that reproduces the issue
-->
```yaml
VAR $FILE_INDEX = 0

LOAD_DS_FILES_FROM_SD()

WHILE ( FILE_INDEX_VALID() == TRUE )
    DISPLAY_PNG /select.png
    DISPLAY_TEXT 0 35 #_FILE_INDEX_FILE_NAME_

    DISPLAY_TEXT 0 55 Click) Next file
    DISPLAY_TEXT 0 65 Hold ) Run

    WAIT_FOR_BUTTON_PRESS

    IF (BUTTON_SHORT_PRESS())
        $FILE_INDEX = ( $FILE_INDEX + 1 )
    ELSE IF (BUTTON_LONG_PRESS())
        DISPLAY_PNG /select.png
        DISPLAY_TEXT 0 35 Run #_FILE_INDEX_FILE_NAME_
        DISPLAY_TEXT 0 45 Are you sure?

        DISPLAY_TEXT 0 55 Click) Back
        DISPLAY_TEXT 0 65 Hold ) Run
        WAIT_FOR_BUTTON_PRESS

        IF (BUTTON_LONG_PRESS() == 1)
            DISPLAY_CLEAR
            RUN_PAYLOAD #_FILE_INDEX_FILE_NAME_
        ELSE
            REM DO NOTHING
        END_IF
    END_IF
END_WHILE

RESTART_PAYLOAD
```

pull_request.title: Add Setting for Default Autoscroll State
pull_request.body:
Currently, the autoscroll state of the song editor and piano roll (continuous, stepped, none) is not saved. This can be an issue for users who want to permanently set their autoscroll settings, without having to change them every time they start up LMMS.

This PR adds an option in the settings window to change the default autoscroll state.
